{"__type":"$$EventMessageAiNode","id":"71cc0af4-dc8b-4bae-80d8-143e0eccf2a6","ts":"2025-10-27T18:58:59.261+01:00","eventName":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","message":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","payload":{"executionId":"145","nodeName":"kimi k2","workflowName":"MCPTestAgents (fetch from graphDB)","nodeType":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGroq","workflowId":"QivgnSMUPDexbVcZ","msg":"{\"messages\":[\"System: You are a helpful assistant that extract informations from the incoming message and searches relevant sources online.\\n\\nStep 1: search online with \\\"Search with Tavily to extract urls\\\"\\nStep 2: filter the resulting urls, removing redundant hits and sorting them by degree of relevance\\nStep 3: Use Fetch to extract the markdown version of the website. \\n\\nStep 4: repeat the procedure (step 1-3) max 4 times. \\n\\nStep 5: return results and their sources. \\nWhich data was more common? \\nWhich one was not found to be founded?\\nHuman: ```json\\n[\\n  {\\n    \\\"projectName\\\": \\\"Luminora Solar Dos & Luminora Solar Tres (TotalEnergies + Soltec)\\\",\\n    \\\"locationName\\\": \\\"Murcia region\\\",\\n    \\\"organizationName\\\": \\\"TotalEnergies + Soltec\\\"\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"projectName\\\": \\\"Luminora Solar Dos & Luminora Solar Tres (TotalEnergies + Soltec)\\\",\\n    \\\"locationName\\\": \\\"Murcia region\\\",\\n    \\\"organizationName\\\": \\\"TotalEnergies + Soltec\\\"\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"projectName\\\": \\\"Entrenúcleos solar park (Plenitude – Eni)\\\",\\n    \\\"locationName\\\": \\\"Seville (Andalusia)\\\",\\n    \\\"organizationName\\\": \\\"Plenitude – Eni\\\"\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"projectName\\\": \\\"Entrenúcleos solar park (Plenitude – Eni)\\\",\\n    \\\"locationName\\\": \\\"Seville (Andalusia)\\\",\\n    \\\"organizationName\\\": \\\"Plenitude – Eni\\\"\\n  },\\n  {\\n    \\\"projectName\\\": \\\"Zaratan (Q ENERGY)\\\",\\n    \\\"locationName\\\": \\\"Castile‑León\\\",\\n    \\\"organizationName\\\": \\\"Q ENERGY\\\"\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\nAI: I'll search for information about these solar projects online. Let me start by searching for details about each project.\\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Luminora Solar Dos Luminora Solar Tres TotalEnergies Soltec Murcia region solar project\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"TotalEnergies and Soltec are constructing three solar projects in Murcia, Spain, with a combined capacity of 315 MW. Construction of the 116 MW plants by Ferrovial and TotalEnergies is expected to finish by late 2026. The projects will supply electricity to over 30,500 homes.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://solarbytes.info/business-bytes/ferrovial-totalenergies-build-116-mw-solar-plants-murcia-spain-9470846\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Murcia to host 116 MW solar plants by Ferrovial, TotalEnergies ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The plants will produce 116 MW of electricity for 30,500 homes. Construction is expected to finish by late 2026.TheLuminora Solar Tres plant is\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.7402687,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.pv-tech.org/totalenergies-and-soltec-authorised-to-construct-200mw-solar-project-in-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"TotalEnergies and Soltec authorised to construct 200MW solar ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Construction of the Luminora Solar Dos PV project will begin in 2024. The project will feature over 337,000 bifacial solar PV modules and more\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.73868835,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://renewablesnow.com/news/totalenergies-soltec-cut-sod-on-315-mw-of-solar-projects-in-spain-1277915/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"TotalEnergies, Soltec cut sod on 315 MW of solar projects in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Soltec Power Holdings SA (BME:SOL) have started construction of two solar farms in Spain's region of Murcia with a combined capacity of 315 MW.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6954834,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.gem.wiki/Luminora_solar_farm\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Luminora solar farm - Global Energy Monitor - GEM.wiki\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Luminora solar farm (Planta solar fotovoltaica Luminora Solar) is a solar photovoltaic (PV) farm in pre-construction in Murcia, Region of Murcia, Spain.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6680367,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://newsroom.ferrovial.com/en/press-releases/ferrovial-to-build-three-photovoltaic-plants-in-murcia-spain-with-capacity-to-supply-30500-homes/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Ferrovial to build three photovoltaic plants in Murcia, Spain, with ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Ferrovial will build three new photovoltaic plants for TotalEnergies and Soltec in Spain's Murcia region. The plants will have a total capacity of 116 MWp.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6512002,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.64,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"ccc2a48e-eef9-4e36-a203-deefe28c0ea9\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Contents of https://solarbytes.info/business-bytes/ferrovial-totalenergies-build-116-mw-solar-plants-murcia-spain-9470846:\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nMurcia to host 116 MW solar plants by Ferrovial, TotalEnergies & Soltec\\\\n\\\\n* Business bytes\\\\n* Market Bytes\\\\n* Tech bytes\\\\n* China Bytes\\\\n* India Bytes\\\\n* America Bytes\\\\n\\\\nAuthors\\\\n\\\\nPowered by\\\\n\\\\n# Murcia to host 116 MW solar plants by Ferrovial, TotalEnergies & Soltec\\\\n\\\\nThree solar plants with 116 MW capacity are being built in Murcia to supply 30,500 homes and cut 4,500 tons of CO2, with Ferrovial, TotalEnergies and Soltec involved.\\\\n\\\\nBy Prudhvi Rani 07 Jul 2025 in Business Bytes Project BytesNew Update\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nThe Luminora Solar Tres plant is planned to provide 95 MW with 150,000 bifacial solar panels. Image Source: Ferrovial\\\\n\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nFerrovial, a company from Spain, is building three solar plants for TotalEnergies and Soltec in Murcia. The plants will produce 116 MW of electricity for 30,500 homes. Construction is expected to finish by late 2026.TheLuminora Solar Tres plant is planned to provide 95 MW with 150,000 bifacial solar panels. It includes a substation and a 5-kilometer overhead line. Fuente Álamo I and II will add 21 MW with 33,000 panels and an 8-kilometer line. Together, the plants are expected to avoid 4,500 tons of CO2 annually. Ferrovial will operate the plants for two years. The project includes weather stations, advanced monitoring, security systems, and grid connection infrastructure.Prior to this project in Murcia, Ferrovial had already taken steps in the US market with a 257 MWdc solar acquisition in Texas.\\\\n\\\\nAdvertisment#Murica #Soltec #TotalEnergies #FerrovialSubscribe to our Newsletter! Be the first to get exclusive offers and the latest newsAdvertisment {'id': '686bad4cb51c880df8065f20', 'source\\\\\\\\_name': 'Ferrovial', 'source\\\\\\\\_link': 'https://newsroom.ferrovial.com/en/press-releases/ferrovial-to-build-three-photovoltaic-plants-in-murcia-spain-with-capacity-to-supply-30500-homes/', 'contact\\\\\\\\_name': '', 'contact\\\\\\\\_email': ''}\\\\n\\\\nRelated Articles\\\\n\\\\nAdvertisment\\\\n\\\\n### Scan to join our channel\\\\n\\\\nLatest StoriesRead the Next ArticleSubscribe to our Newsletter!Be the first to get exclusive offers and the latest news\\\\n\\\\nSolar Bytes brings you the latest news in solar world in bite size; essentially a gist of important solar news in few sentences.\\\\n\\\\nSubscribe to our Newsletter!\\\\n\\\\nQuick Links\\\\n\\\\n* Disclaimer\\\\n* Privacy\\\\n* Contact\\\\n\\\\nPowered by\\\\n\\\\n\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Entrenúcleos solar park Plenitude Eni Seville Andalusia solar project\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Entrenúcleos solar park in Andalusia, initiated by Plenitude, is a 200 MW photovoltaic plant set to deliver over 435 GWh annually from 2026. It consists of four solar plants: Granville, Killington, Plumlee, and Rickwood. Construction began in 2025.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://energynews.pro/en/plenitude-starts-200-mw-solar-park-in-andalusia-for-2026/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude starts 200 MW solar park in Andalusia for 2026\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Italian group Plenitude has begun building Entrenúcleos, a 200 MW photovoltaic plant near Seville, set to deliver more than 435 GWh a year from 2026.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8755427,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://renewablesnow.com/news/plenitude-starts-building-200-mw-solar-park-in-spain-1277995/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude starts building 200-MW solar park in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Entrenucleos marks Plenitude's third plant under construction in Andalusia, adding to the 230-MW Guillena project in Seville and the 150-MW\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.85509074,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://iberianlawyer.com/plenitude-begins-construction-of-a-new-200-mw-solar-plant-in-seville-advisors/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude begins construction of a new 200 MW solar plant ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Entrenúcleos is the third plant that Plenitude is building in Andalusia, adding to the 230 MW in Guillena (Seville) and the 150 MW in\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.82391036,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.power-technology.com/news/plenitude-200mw-pv-project-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude begins construction of 200MW PV project in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Entrenúcleos solar park is designed to consist of four plants: Granville, Killington, Plumlee and Rickwood.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.79369855,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.rigzone.com/news/plenitude_starts_new_pv_park_construction_in_seville-07-jul-2025-181057-article/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Plenitude Starts New PV Park Construction in Seville\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Entrenucleos, anticipated to be operational in 2026, will feature four solar plants: Granville, Killington, Plumlee, and Rickwood. Each will\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.7621591,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.61,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"56a40f1e-c9e9-40c4-aeb9-ef0571034640\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Contents of https://energynews.pro/en/plenitude-starts-200-mw-solar-park-in-andalusia-for-2026/:\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nPlenitude Starts 200 MW Solar Park In Andalusia For 2026 - Energynews.pro\\\\n\\\\nSkip to content\\\\n\\\\nSUBSCRIBE\\\\n\\\\n* English\\\\n* Français\\\\n\\\\n* English\\\\n* Français\\\\n## © XMARKET PUBLISHING\\\\n\\\\n* Solar Energy\\\\n* | Corporate Investment\\\\n# Plenitude starts 200 MW solar park in Andalusia for 2026\\\\n\\\\nItalian group Plenitude has begun building Entrenúcleos, a 200 MW photovoltaic plant near Seville, set to deliver more than 435 GWh a year from 2026 while trialling locally produced green steel.\\\\n## Share:\\\\n\\\\n* energynews\\\\n* July, 7 2025\\\\n## Comprehensive energy news coverage, updated nonstop\\\\n\\\\n## Annual subscription\\\\n\\\\n## 8.25€/month\\\\\\\\*\\\\n\\\\n## \\\\\\\\*billed annually at 99€/year for the first year then 149,00€/year\\\\n\\\\n## Unlimited access • Archives included • Professional invoice\\\\n\\\\nSUBSCRIBE - 99€/year\\\\n## OTHER ACCESS OPTIONS\\\\n\\\\n## Monthly subscription\\\\n\\\\n## Unlimited access • Archives included\\\\n\\\\n## 5.2€/month\\\\\\\\* then 14.90€ per month thereafter\\\\n\\\\n## FREE ACCOUNT\\\\n\\\\n## 3 articles offered per month\\\\n\\\\n## FREE\\\\n\\\\n## \\\\\\\\*Prices are excluding VAT, which may vary depending on your location or professional status\\\\n\\\\n## Since 2021: 35,000 articles • 150+ analyses per week\\\\n\\\\nPlenitude, a subsidiary of Italy’s Eni SpA, has driven the first pile for the Entrenúcleos solar park twenty kilometres from Seville. Scheduled for 2026, the 200 MW facility is expected to supply over 435 GWh of electricity a year, matching the annual demand of about one hundred and thirty thousand Spanish households. Straddling Dos Hermanas and Coria del Río, the plant covers more than 300 hectares. The company estimates the build will peak at three hundred direct jobs.\\\\n\\\\nSchedule, capacity and connection The complex consists of four fifty-megawatt-peak sections—Granville, Killington, Plumlee and Rickwood—housing 326 000 bifacial panels. Their output will flow through the Entrenúcleos SET substation to the national grid via Red Eléctrica Española (REE). Plenitude says the layout curbs losses and eases access. Solarig has secured the engineering, procurement and construction contract.\\\\n\\\\nThe company will test green-steel structures, a recycled Spanish material with zero carbon footprint. Plenitude aims to shorten its supply chain and hedge against imported metal price swings. Permits also require ecological corridors and biodiversity islands for steppe birds, while land equal to the module footprint will host extensive farming practices.\\\\n\\\\nAndalusian portfolio and strategy Entrenúcleos lifts to 580 MW the solar capacity Plenitude is building in Andalusia, alongside Guillena (230 MW) and Caparacena (150 MW). “This plant confirms our ambition in Spain,” said Mariangiola Mollicone, managing director of Plenitude Renewables Spain and head of renewable energy for Western Europe. The group claims more than sixty thousand residential customers in the region. Its national operating portfolio stands at 1 300 MW, with a project pipeline above 2 GW.\\\\n\\\\nThe Junta de Andalucía welcomed the investment. “Renewables are the industrial opportunity the region has been waiting for,” stated Manuel Larrasa, secretary-general for energy at the regional Ministry of Industry, Energy and Mines. Dos Hermanas mayor Francisco Rodríguez called the initiative “a job creator” and “an element of industrial positioning” for the city. Works are slated for twenty-four months, with local procurement valued above EUR150 mn ($163 mn).\\\\n\\\\n* Popular on energynews.pro\\\\n\\\\n* Business strategy\\\\nAltano Energy raises €81mn to develop five hybrid projects in Andalusia\\\\n\\\\n* Monday 27 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Nuclear Energy\\\\nAlmaraz operators request extension beyond 2028\\\\n\\\\n* Monday 27 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Natural Gas\\\\nCMA CGM orders six LNG container ships from India’s Cochin Shipyard\\\\n\\\\n* Tuesday 21 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Oil\\\\nChevron and Helleniq Energy secure four offshore exploration permits in Greece\\\\n\\\\n* Monday 27 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Energy Policy\\\\nCameroon to exempt biofuel equipment from customs duties starting 2026 to boost the sector\\\\n\\\\n* Monday 27 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Solar Energy\\\\nUAE launches $6bn project for 1GW of continuous renewable energyAbu Dhabi has begun construction on the world’s first gigascale solar and battery storage project, capable of delivering 1GW of baseload renewable power, with operations expected by 2027.\\\\n\\\\n* Monday 27 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Solar Energy\\\\nShanghai Electric signs 342 MW deal with Econergy in RomaniaShanghai Electric has signed phase II of the Parau photovoltaic project with Econergy, expanding its Romanian solar portfolio to 550 MW.\\\\n\\\\n* Monday 27 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Solar Energy\\\\nSwift Solar deploys first perovskite solar panels for US military operationsSwift Solar has installed its perovskite solar panels on a military site for the first time, as part of a US Department of Defense exercise testing energy resilience for critical infrastructure.\\\\n\\\\n* Monday 27 October 2025\\\\n\\\\n* Solar Energy\\\\nMitsubishi Logistics signs 8MW solar VPPA with JERA CrossMitsubishi Logistics has signed a virtual power purchase agreement with JERA Cross for 8MW of solar power, marking a new step in its energy\\\\n\\\\n<error>Content truncated. Call the fetch tool with a start_index of 5000 to get more content.</error>\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Zaratan Q ENERGY Castile León solar project\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"The Zaratan Q ENERGY project in Castile-León, Spain, is a 96 MWp solar PV project. It powers 50,000 households and reduces 33,000 tonnes of CO2 annually. The project includes battery storage.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://qenergy.eu/media/detail/q-energy-builds-a-further-96-mwp-pv-project-in-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Q ENERGY builds a further 96 MWp PV project in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The 96 MWp \\\\\\\"Zaratan\\\\\\\" project in Castile-Leon, Spain, will power 50,000 households, save 33,000 tonnes of CO2, and has battery storage.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8708723,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.power-technology.com/news/q-energy-attains-financial-close-solar-portfolio/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Q ENERGY attains financial close on 252MWp solar portfolio in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Zaratan cluster, located in Castile and León, consists of three adjacent solar plants. This will generate adequate electricity for\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.82220376,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://finance.yahoo.com/news/q-energy-attains-financial-close-092714928.html\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Q ENERGY attains financial close on 252MWp solar portfolio in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Zaratan cluster, located in Castile and León, consists of three adjacent solar plants. This will generate adequate electricity for\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.82220376,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.enerdatics.com/insights/q-energy-secures-financing-to-power-taurus-b-solar-and-battery-storage-portfolio-in-spain\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Q ENERGY secures financing for Taurus B solar and storage ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"... solar project consisting of three PV plants, and the 96 MW Zaratan cluster in Castile and Leon developed as a single platform. By coupling solar generation\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.7992077,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.renewableenergymagazine.com/pv_solar/q-energy-builds-a-96-mwp-pv-20250505\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Q ENERGY Builds a 96 MWp PV Project in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The project will be built in the Spanish region of Castile-Leon, west of Valladolid, spanning a total area of 163 hectares. Development of co-\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.7722049,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.64,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"b66b8de5-1f6a-4e83-9263-335ed2767945\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Contents of https://qenergy.eu/media/detail/q-energy-builds-a-further-96-mwp-pv-project-in-spain/:\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nQ ENERGY builds a further 96 MWp PV project in Spain - Q ENERGY\\\\n\\\\nSkip to main content\\\\n\\\\nEN\\\\n\\\\n* EN\\\\n* DE\\\\n* FR\\\\n* ES\\\\n* PT\\\\n* IT\\\\n\\\\n* About Q ENERGY\\\\n  \\\\n  + Who We Are\\\\n  + Our Purpose & Values\\\\n  + Our Executive Team\\\\n* Business Areas\\\\n  \\\\n  + Solar\\\\n  + Agrivoltaics\\\\n  + Wind Onshore\\\\n  + Wind Offshore\\\\n  + Repowering\\\\n  + BESS - Battery Energy Storage Solutions\\\\n  + Green Hydrogen\\\\n* You Are...\\\\n  \\\\n  + Municipalities\\\\n  + Investors\\\\n  + Landowners\\\\n  + Farmers\\\\n  + Industry & Commerce\\\\n* Land Lease Configurator\\\\n* Sustainability\\\\n* News and Media\\\\n* Career\\\\n* Contact\\\\n\\\\nQENERGY Solutions SE Q ENERGY Europe GmbH\\\\n\\\\nHildegard-Knef-Platz 3 10829 Berlin GERMANY\\\\n\\\\ninfo@qenergy.eu\\\\n\\\\n+49 30 88 92 78-0\\\\n\\\\nQENERGY France SAS\\\\n\\\\nZA de Courtine, 330 Rue du Mourelet 84000 Avignon FRANCE\\\\n\\\\nqef-info@qenergy.eu\\\\n\\\\n+33 04 32 76 03 00\\\\n\\\\nQ ENERGY Europe GmbH\\\\n\\\\nPaseo de la Castellana 95, 13th floor 28046 Madrid SPAIN\\\\n\\\\nadmin\\\\\\\\_es@qenergy.eu\\\\n\\\\n+34 916670139\\\\n\\\\n* LinkedIn\\\\n* YouTube\\\\n\\\\n* English\\\\n* German\\\\n* French\\\\n* Spanish\\\\n* Portuguese\\\\n* Italian\\\\n\\\\nQENERGY Solutions SE Q ENERGY Europe GmbH\\\\n\\\\nHildegard-Knef-Platz 3 10829 Berlin GERMANY\\\\n\\\\ninfo@qenergy.eu\\\\n\\\\n+49 30 88 92 78-0\\\\n\\\\nQENERGY France SAS\\\\n\\\\nZA de Courtine, 330 Rue du Mourelet 84000 Avignon FRANCE\\\\n\\\\nqef-info@qenergy.eu\\\\n\\\\n+33 04 32 76 03 00\\\\n\\\\nQ ENERGY Europe GmbH\\\\n\\\\nPaseo de la Castellana 95, 13th floor 28046 Madrid SPAIN\\\\n\\\\nadmin\\\\\\\\_es@qenergy.eu\\\\n\\\\n+34 916670139\\\\n\\\\n05.05.2025\\\\n\\\\n# Q ENERGY builds a further 96 MWp PV project in Spain\\\\n\\\\n* Expected to cover the annual electricity needs of 50,000 households\\\\n* Large-scale BESS hybridisation under development\\\\n* Completion scheduled for year-end 2026\\\\n* 6th Spanish Q ENERGY project started in 2025\\\\n\\\\nBerlin/Madrid, 29^th April 2025. Q ENERGY is rapidly advancing the realisation of its PV pipeline in Spain and has started the construction of a further solar power project with a global capacity of 96 MWp. The “Zaratan” project consists of three adjacent solar plants and will generate enough fossil-free electricity to supply nearly 50,000 Spanish households with green energy, saving 33,000 tonnes of CO2 annually. The PV plants are expected to be completed by the end of 2026.\\\\n\\\\nThe project will be built in the Spanish region of Castile-Leon, west of Valladolid, spanning a total area of 163 hectares. Development of co-located battery storage is also under way, which is expected to materially increase the value of the plant’s electricity output. The BESS portfolio will consist of three 4-hour BESS units, one for each PV plant.\\\\n\\\\nAt Q ENERGY we are committed to environmentally responsible project development and the harmonious integration of our facilities into the natural landscape. Once completed, the three PV fields will be surrounded by a green belt of native hedgerows and trees, creating a habitat for local wildlife. Insect hotels and nesting aids for birds of prey, such as buzzards and kestrels, will support local biodiversity on site. The grassland between the modules will continue to be used as grazing land for cattle, supporting sustainable land use and local agriculture.\\\\n\\\\n> Mauro di Fiore, Head of Q ENERGY’s EPC Division, says: ‘With this sixth project, we have already started the construction of projects totalling more than 400 MWp in 2025 alone. We are proud to see how quickly our development pipeline is coming to fruition and we will continue to expand our EPC capacity in the coming months, also by involving local companies.’\\\\n\\\\n### Media Contact\\\\n\\\\nQ ENERGY Solutions SE External Communications Amanda Baudry, Christian Köhn media@qenergy.eu www.qenergy.eu\\\\n\\\\n### Safe-Harbor Statement\\\\n\\\\nThis press release contains forward-looking statements. These forward-looking statements can be identified by terminology such as \\\\\\\"will,\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"expects,\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"anticipates,\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"future,\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"intends,\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"plans,\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"believes,\\\\\\\" \\\\\\\"estimates\\\\\\\" and similar statements. Among other things, the quotations from management in this press release and Q ENERGY’s operations and business outlook, contain forward-looking statements. Such statements involve certain risks and uncertainties that could cause actual results to differ materially from those expressed in or suggested by the forward-looking statements. Except as required by law, Q ENERGY does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statements, whether as a result of new information, future events or otherwise.\\\\n\\\\n### About Q ENERGY\\\\n\\\\nQ ENERGY is Europe's provider of holistic solutions for green power plants. The company is active along the entire value chain of renewable energy projects - from solar parks, onshore and offshore wind projects to energy storage solutions and hybrid power plants. More than 550 employees in the Berlin headquarters and further international offices are currently driving a development pipeline of +11 GW across Europe. Building on more than 25 years of experience and 2.5 GW completed renewable energy assets, Q ENERGY is currently active in Spain, Portugal, France, and Germany as well as in Italy. Together with its independent sister company Hanwha Qcells, \\\\n\\\\n<error>Content truncated. Call the fetch tool with a start_index of 5000 to get more content.</error>\\\"}]\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"Let me search for more specific details about the TotalEnergies and Soltec partnership:\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"tool_calls\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":68,\"promptTokens\":6359,\"totalTokens\":6427}}}"}}
