{"__type":"$$EventMessageAiNode","id":"df437d3a-7ab8-4fb6-8013-48f39dae43e0","ts":"2025-10-27T19:22:15.403+01:00","eventName":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","message":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","payload":{"executionId":"146","nodeName":"groq-openai-120b2","workflowName":"graph-knowledge-agent","nodeType":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGroq","workflowId":"aS5r9ljDR7IaUyFE","msg":"{\"messages\":[\"System: # ROLE\\n\\nYou are a **Research Agent** with access to **Tavily Search** (search results) and **Fetch** (full page). Your mission is to discover **permits, approvals, grants, subsidies, and financing events** for **utility-scale solar and wind farms scheduled to start construction in 2026**.\\n\\n# BEHAVIOR\\n\\n* The **geographic area** of interest will be provided by the user.\\n* Run up to **5 Tavily searches**. After each search, review the snippets.\\n* When a result looks relevant or promising, **call Fetch** on the page to read the full content.\\n* Use varied angles: government approvals, regulatory filings, EIAs, planning consents, grid connection approvals, auctions/tenders, developer press releases, financial closes, loans, grants/subsidies.\\n* Prefer **official and primary sources** (regulators, government gazettes, banks, developers).\\n* Deduplicate projects by name/country; merge evidence from multiple sources.\\n* Exclude vague announcements that don’t specify **2026 construction start**.\\n\\n# MOST IMPORTANT INFO TO COLLECT PER PROJECT\\n\\n* **Project identity**: name, developer/owner, location (country, region, site).\\n* **Technology**: solar PV, CSP, onshore wind, offshore wind, or hybrid.\\n* **Capacity**: announced or approved MW size.\\n* **Construction schedule**: explicit evidence of 2026 start (quote, phrasing, or official document).\\n* **Permits & approvals**: EIA, planning consent, grid connection approval, other regulatory milestones.\\n* **Grants & subsidies**: public programs, awarded auctions/tenders, subsidy amounts.\\n* **Financing**: loans, bonds, equity investments, financial close announcements (amount, lender/investor, status).\\n* **Notable contractors**: EPC, turbine supplier, or technology provider if named.\\n* **Source details**: title, publisher, URL, publication date.\\n* **Confidence level**: how strong the evidence is (official vs media vs rumor).\\nHuman: Spain\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Spain utility scale solar project construction 2026 permit\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Spain authorized construction of 25GW of solar PV capacity in 2026. The Limonero Solar PV Park is expected to start construction in 2026. Utility-scale solar projects are set to increase by 25% in 2026.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.power-technology.com/data-insights/power-plant-profile-limonero-solar-pv-park-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Power plant profile: Limonero Solar PV Park, Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Limonero Solar PV Park is a ground-mounted solar project. Development status. The project construction is expected to commence from 2026.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8018276,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://newprojectmedia.com/spain-solaer-acquires-100-mw-solar-project-financing-in-the-offing/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Solaer acquires 100 MW solar project, financing in the offing\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Construction of the project has commenced following receipt of all necessary permits. Completion is expected by March 2026, with grid connection scheduled\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.666736,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.pv-tech.org/spain-authorises-construction-25gw-solar-pv-capacity/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Spain authorises construction of 25GW of solar PV capacity\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Spanish Ministry of Ecological Transition (MITECO) has authorised the construction of nearly 25GW of solar PV capacity to be built in Spain.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.5504388,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.pv-tech.org/utility-scale-solar-installs-in-spain-to-jump-25-but-renewables-auctions-not-so-attractive-unef/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Utility-scale solar installs in Spain to jump 25% but ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Spain is set to install more than 4GW of utility-scale solar in 2022, according to José Donoso, head of the country's PV association, UNEF.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.40570828,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://inspenet.com/en/noticias/naturgy-battery-storage-for-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Naturgy battery storage for Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"This initiative is part of a total portfolio of 10 projects that will be operational by 2026. European investment for a real energy transition.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.39894548,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://strategicenergy.eu/over-5-gw-of-solar-projects-entered-permitting-in-spain-during-2025/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Over 5 GW of solar projects entered permitting in Spain ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Castilla-La Mancha was the most chosen location, with 1,924 MW submitted, while Zelestra led the ranking of developers thanks to the REINA mega-project totalling 887 MW. Renewable energy developers submitted a portfolio of **5,141 MW of large-scale solar projects** for environmental permitting across various autonomous communities during the first seven months of 2025, consolidating the expansion of the photovoltaic sector in the country. Currently, the country has **35,632 MW of solar capacity in operation**, and in the first seven months of 2025 alone, **3,029 MW** were commissioned — a promising yet demanding pace. Finally, it is worth noting that over the past 12 months, more than **33 GW of solar projects** have been submitted for permitting, including small-scale developments managed by regional authorities.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.3962089,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.energy-box.com/post/mcpv-secures-10m-grant-for-2-5gw-solar-module-plant-in-spain\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"MCPV Secures €10M Grant for 2.5GW Solar Module Plant ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Construction is expected to start in 2027, following the launch of a 4 GW solar cell plant in Veendam, the Netherlands, in late 2026. Permitting\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.24366534,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_power_in_Spain\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Solar power in Spain\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Jump to content ## Contents Edit links Spain has been cited as a model in how not to develop renewables. * An isolated mountain hut with stand-alone PV system in Catalonia | Mula Photovoltaic Power Plant | 494 | Completed July 2019 | PV capacity in watts per capita by autonomous communities in 2013 | Castile-La Mancha | 897 | 923 | 4,048 | 1,974 | This policy triggered the production of this type of renewable energy positioning Spain on top of the largest producers of photovoltaic electricity in the world by 2009. * List of renewable energy topics by country | * Portal * Category |\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.16162466,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.pv-magazine.com/2025/10/08/spain-installs-7-2-gw-of-solar-in-2024-amid-rooftop-slowdown/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Spain installs 7.2 GW of solar in 2024 amid rooftop slowdown\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Spain added 7.2 GW of new solar capacity in 2024, bringing total installations to more than 40 GW, though rooftop deployment fell sharply,\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.15683989,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://strategicenergy.eu/september-accelerates-170-mw-of-renewables-hybridisation-and-batteries-gain-ground-in-spain/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"September accelerates 170 MW of renewables\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The MITECO is processing seven renewable projects from Iberdrola, Boreas Energy, Naturgy, Siemens Gamesa and Sistemas Energéticos, involving hybridisation, batteries and repowering in Cáceres, Burgos, Aragón, Navarra, Ciudad Real and Zaragoza. Meanwhile, **Burgos** adds **30 MW of storage** with the **BESS HIB PE Iglesias project**, promoted by **Boreas Energy**, to be **hybridised** with the **70.4 MW Iglesias wind farm** and its **evacuation facilities**. In addition, **simplified environmental assessments** were issued for the **19.1 MW FV Hibridación El Valle PV project** in **Navarra**, promoted by **Sistemas Energéticos**; the **Malagón II PV module** to be **hybridised** with the existing **Malagón II wind farm** in **Ciudad Real**, promoted by **Naturgy**; and the **Boyal I and II wind repowering projects** (each **5 MW**) in **Zaragoza and Navarra**, promoted by **Siemens Gamesa Renewable Energy**.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.08016299,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.64,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"da9b23f4-78d0-4b39-90b5-7d37dac4b0a8\\\"}]\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"openai/gpt-oss-120b\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"tool_calls\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":111,\"promptTokens\":2240,\"totalTokens\":2351}}}"}}
