s, bonds, equity investments, financial close announcements (amount, lender/investor, status).\\n* **Notable contractors**: EPC, turbine supplier, or technology provider if named.\\n* **Source details**: title, publisher, URL, publication date.\\n* **Confidence level**: how strong the evidence is (official vs media vs rumor).\\nHuman: Chile\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Chile solar farm construction start 2026 permit\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Chile's construction of a solar farm is set to start in April 2026. The project is part of a USD-500m initiative. It will enter commercial operation by 2028.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://renewablesnow.com/news/chiles-colbun-starts-permitting-for-usd-500m-solar-bess-project-1268796/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile's Colbun starts permitting for USD-500m solar, BESS ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Chile's Colbun starts permitting for USD-500m solar, BESS project ... Construction is planned to commence in April 2026, according to the plan.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8790744,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://list.solar/news/colbun-initiates/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Colbun Initiates $500M Solar and Storage Project in Chile\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Construction Start Date: Scheduled to commence in April 2026. Operational Timeline: Expected to start operations in 2028, aligning with Chile's\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8655088,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.power-technology.com/data-insights/power-plant-profile-gabriela-solar-pv-park-chile/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Power plant profile: Gabriela Solar PV Park, Chile\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The project construction is expected to commence from 2026. Subsequent to that it will enter into commercial operation by 2027. For more\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.82694983,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.ess-news.com/2025/10/03/chiles-900-mwh-kronos-storage-project-enters-environmental-assessment/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile's 900 MWh Kronos storage project enters environmental ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Construction of Kronos is set to begin on Nov. 30, 2026, with operations to start in November 2027. The 35-year facility would employ a\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.7640656,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://freepowergroup.com/news/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"News\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Zaldívar Photovoltaic Park Secures Environmental Approval and Prepares for Construction in 2026. The project, located in the Antofagasta Region and co\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.75268626,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://renewablesnow.com/news/chiles-enap-says-green-h2-plant-72-percent-complete-start-up-due-early-2026-1283536/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile's Enap says green H2 plant 72% complete, start-up ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Chile's Enap says green H2 plant 72% complete, start-up due early 2026 ... project's design and construction. The facility will produce about\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6615081,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.energy-box.com/post/colbun-begins-permitting-for-usd-500m-solar-and-bess-project-in-chile\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Colbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# Colbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS Project in Chile * Energy Box Chilean utility Colbun SA has started the environmental permitting process for its Encanto power project in the O'Higgins region. The project aims to develop a 249.7-MWp solar farm coupled with a 260-MW battery energy storage system (BESS). The total investment for this project is estimated at USD 500 million (EUR 480.6m), based on Colbun’s permit application. Located on private land in the Marchigue commune, the project will feature over 349,000 photovoltaic modules and a battery storage capacity of 1,040 MWh, along with a substation and transmission line. DAS Solar Expands Global Footprint with 230MW Projects in Germany RENEWABLE ENERGY ENERGY STO