{"__type":"$$EventMessageAiNode","id":"2a20167f-ddc6-42c2-9b8e-c74838a3e82b","ts":"2025-10-28T20:11:04.188+01:00","eventName":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","message":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","payload":{"executionId":"149","nodeName":"Groq-kimik2","workflowName":"graph-knowledge-agent","nodeType":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGroq","workflowId":"aS5r9ljDR7IaUyFE","msg":"{\"messages\":[\"System: # ROLE\\n\\nYou are a **Research Agent** with access to **Tavily Search** (search results) and **Fetch** (full page). Your mission is to discover **permits, approvals, grants, subsidies, and financing events** for **utility-scale solar and wind farms scheduled to start construction in 2026**.\\n\\n# BEHAVIOR\\n\\n* The **geographic area** of interest will be provided by the user.\\n* Run up to **5 Tavily searches**. After each search, review the snippets.\\n* When a result looks relevant or promising, **call Fetch** on the page to read the full content.\\n* Use varied angles: government approvals, regulatory filings, EIAs, planning consents, grid connection approvals, auctions/tenders, developer press releases, financial closes, loans, grants/subsidies.\\n* Prefer **official and primary sources** (regulators, government gazettes, banks, developers).\\n* Deduplicate projects by name/country; merge evidence from multiple sources.\\n* Exclude vague announcements that don’t specify **2026 construction start**.\\n\\n# MOST IMPORTANT INFO TO COLLECT PER PROJECT\\n\\n* **Project identity**: name, developer/owner, location (country, region, site).\\n* **Technology**: solar PV, CSP, onshore wind, offshore wind, or hybrid.\\n* **Capacity**: announced or approved MW size.\\n* **Construction schedule**: explicit evidence of 2026 start (quote, phrasing, or official document).\\n* **Permits & approvals**: EIA, planning consent, grid connection approval, other regulatory milestones.\\n* **Grants & subsidies**: public programs, awarded auctions/tenders, subsidy amounts.\\n* **Financing**: loans, bonds, equity investments, financial close announcements (amount, lender/investor, status).\\n* **Notable contractors**: EPC, turbine supplier, or technology provider if named.\\n* **Source details**: title, publisher, URL, publication date.\\n* **Confidence level**: how strong the evidence is (official vs media vs rumor).\\nHuman: Chile\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Chile solar farm construction start 2026 permit\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"Chile's construction of a solar farm is set to start in April 2026. The project is part of a USD-500m initiative. It will enter commercial operation by 2028.\\\",\\\"images\\\":[],\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://renewablesnow.com/news/chiles-colbun-starts-permitting-for-usd-500m-solar-bess-project-1268796/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile's Colbun starts permitting for USD-500m solar, BESS ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Chile's Colbun starts permitting for USD-500m solar, BESS project ... Construction is planned to commence in April 2026, according to the plan.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8790744,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://list.solar/news/colbun-initiates/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Colbun Initiates $500M Solar and Storage Project in Chile\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Construction Start Date: Scheduled to commence in April 2026. Operational Timeline: Expected to start operations in 2028, aligning with Chile's\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.8655088,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.power-technology.com/data-insights/power-plant-profile-gabriela-solar-pv-park-chile/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Power plant profile: Gabriela Solar PV Park, Chile\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The project construction is expected to commence from 2026. Subsequent to that it will enter into commercial operation by 2027. For more\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.82694983,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.ess-news.com/2025/10/03/chiles-900-mwh-kronos-storage-project-enters-environmental-assessment/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile's 900 MWh Kronos storage project enters environmental ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Construction of Kronos is set to begin on Nov. 30, 2026, with operations to start in November 2027. The 35-year facility would employ a\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.7640656,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://freepowergroup.com/news/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"News\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Zaldívar Photovoltaic Park Secures Environmental Approval and Prepares for Construction in 2026. The project, located in the Antofagasta Region and co\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.75268626,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://renewablesnow.com/news/chiles-enap-says-green-h2-plant-72-percent-complete-start-up-due-early-2026-1283536/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile's Enap says green H2 plant 72% complete, start-up ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Chile's Enap says green H2 plant 72% complete, start-up due early 2026 ... project's design and construction. The facility will produce about\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6615081,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.energy-box.com/post/colbun-begins-permitting-for-usd-500m-solar-and-bess-project-in-chile\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Colbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# Colbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS Project in Chile * Energy Box Chilean utility Colbun SA has started the environmental permitting process for its Encanto power project in the O'Higgins region. The project aims to develop a 249.7-MWp solar farm coupled with a 260-MW battery energy storage system (BESS). The total investment for this project is estimated at USD 500 million (EUR 480.6m), based on Colbun’s permit application. Located on private land in the Marchigue commune, the project will feature over 349,000 photovoltaic modules and a battery storage capacity of 1,040 MWh, along with a substation and transmission line. DAS Solar Expands Global Footprint with 230MW Projects in Germany RENEWABLE ENERGY ENERGY STORAGE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6504012,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.pvknowhow.com/news/canadian-solar-chile-energy-storage-2026/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Canadian Solar Chile to Deliver 912 MWh Energy Storage ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# Canadian Solar Chile to Deliver 912 MWh Energy Storage by 2026 ## Canadian Solar Chile’s Landmark Solar Project: A New Era in Renewable Energy In partnership with Travesía Solar, a Chilean solar developer, Canadian Solar will supply an impressive 912 MWh energy storage system, seamlessly integrated with the 600 MWp Santa Isabel solar power project. ## Canadian Solar Chile Leads with the Country’s Largest Solar Power Project Set to become Chile’s largest solar power facility, this Canadian Solar project is pioneering in integrating energy storage. Canadian Solar has a distinguished record of developing large-scale solar projects and energy storage solutions globally. As Chile expands its renewable energy capacity, Canadian Solar’s expertise in energy storage will be instrumental in supporting the country’s energy transition.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.6063825,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.ess-news.com/2025/07/31/rwes-massive-1277-mwh-solar-plus-storage-project-in-chile-secures-environmental-approval/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"RWE's massive 1277 MWh solar plus storage project in Chile ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# RWE’s massive 1,277 MWh solar plus storage project in Chile secures environmental approval German energy firm RWE has received environmental approval for its the Los Durmientes solar and storage plant. The project, located in the Antofagasta region of Chile, has a 243.6 MW solar farm co-located with 255.4 MW / 1,277 MWh battery energy storage system (BESS). **pv magazine Week Europe 2025** brings together leading voices from the solar and storage industries to explore what’s next for the European energy transition. ****pv magazine USA**** is hosting the second edition of its multi-day virtual event, focused on advancing U.S. solar and energy storage markets. RWE is expanding its battery storage business with an innovative technology for grid stability.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.3085344,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.bnamericas.com/en/news/chile-us2bn-clean-energy-projects-submitted-for-environmental-review\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile US$2bn clean energy projects submitted...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Chile US$2bn clean energy projects submitted for environmental review - BNamericas Image 1: Logo BNamericas *    Industries  Industries Electric PowerMining & MetalsOil & GasInfrastructureWater & WastePetrochemicalsICTFinancial Services  *   Companies Image 6: Chile Chile US$2bn clean energy projects submitted for environmental review Image 7: Projects Image 8: Contacts Image 9: Companies 83,000+**key contacts** related to companies and projects Image 10: News *     United States+1 *     Congo (Republic) (Congo-Brazzaville)+242 *     Guinea (Guinée)+224 *     Papua New Guinea+675 *     Saint Barthélemy+590 *     Saint Helena+290 *     Saint Lucia+1 *     Saint Martin (Saint-Martin (partie française))+590 *     South Korea (대한민국)+82 *     South Sudan (‫جنوب السودان‬‎)+211 *     United Arab Emirates (‫الإمارات العربية المتحدة‬‎)+971 *     United Kingdom+44 Company Name*   Image 11: BNamericas #### Products *   Companies #### Industries\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.16840546,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":2.58,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"ee3ad830-6583-401f-8c45-021d050735ba\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: When fetching robots.txt (https://renewablesnow.com/robots.txt), received status 403 so assuming that autonomous fetching is not allowed, the user can try manually fetching by using the fetch prompt\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"query\\\":\\\"Colbun solar project April 2026 construction start permit\\\",\\\"follow_up_questions\\\":null,\\\"answer\\\":\\\"The Colbun solar project is scheduled to start construction in April 2026. The project involves a USD-500m solar a