p.co.uk/projects/magellanes-chile/\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Gente Grande Magallanes, Chile\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"The Gente Grande project in Magallanes, Chile, uses wind power for green ammonia production, with a 3GW capacity, and is in the permitting phase.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.43597415,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.energy-box.com/post/colbun-begins-permitting-for-usd-500m-solar-and-bess-project-in-chile\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Colbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS ...\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"# Colbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS Project in Chile * Energy Box Chilean utility Colbun SA has started the environmental permitting process for its Encanto power project in the O'Higgins region. The project aims to develop a 249.7-MWp solar farm coupled with a 260-MW battery energy storage system (BESS). The total investment for this project is estimated at USD 500 million (EUR 480.6m), based on Colbun’s permit application. Located on private land in the Marchigue commune, the project will feature over 349,000 photovoltaic modules and a battery storage capacity of 1,040 MWh, along with a substation and transmission line. DAS Solar Expands Global Footprint with 230MW Projects in Germany RENEWABLE ENERGY ENERGY STORAGE\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.3753177,\\\"raw_content\\\":null},{\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.bnamericas.com/en/features/chiles-10-biggest-early-works-phase-wind-projects\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Chile's 10 biggest early-works phase wind projects\\\",\\\"content\\\":\\\"Chile's 10 biggest early-works phase wind projects - BNamericas Image 7: Chile's 10 biggest early-works phase wind projects Capex associated with Chile’s 10 largest early-stage wind power projects by installed capacity totals US$9.35 billion (bn), according to BNamericas data. Image 8Capex of the 10 biggest early-works phase wind projects in Chile by region (CREDIT: BNamericas) Image 9Installed capacity of the 10 biggest early-works phase wind projects in C