eepers and rails, in the remaining months of this year prepares the second stage of this process that contemplates the recovery of stations, the automation of crossings and the purchase of four trains.\\\",\\\"score\\\":0.06449435,\\\"raw_content\\\":null}],\\\"response_time\\\":1.43,\\\"request_id\\\":\\\"03308abd-b814-4388-a9e8-b4d5334bd2ea\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Contents of https://www.power-technology.com/data-insights/power-plant-profile-gabriela-solar-pv-park-chile/:\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nPower plant profile: Gabriela Solar PV Park, Chile\\\\n\\\\nSkip to site menu Skip to page content\\\\n\\\\nPTMenuSearch\\\\n\\\\n* Data Insights\\\\n\\\\nUpdated October 21, 2024\\\\n# Power plant profile: Gabriela Solar PV Park, Chile\\\\n\\\\nBrought to you by\\\\n\\\\nShare\\\\n\\\\n* Copy Link\\\\n* Share on X\\\\n* Share on Linkedin\\\\n* Share on Facebook\\\\n\\\\nGabriela Solar PV Park is a 220MW solar PV power project. It is planned in Antofagasta, Chile. According to GlobalData, who tracks and profiles over 170,000 power plants worldwide, the project is currently at the permitting stage. It will be developed in a single phase. The project construction is likely to commence in 2026 and is expected to enter into commercial operation in 2027. Buy the profile here.\\\\n\\\\n## Smarter leaders trust GlobalData\\\\n\\\\n## Data Insights Gabriela Solar PV Park\\\\n\\\\nBuy the Profile\\\\n\\\\n##### Data Insights\\\\n\\\\nThe gold standard of business intelligence.\\\\n\\\\nFind out more\\\\n\\\\n#### Discover B2B Marketing That Performs\\\\n\\\\nCombine business intelligence and editorial excellence to reach engaged professionals across 36 leading media platforms.\\\\n\\\\nFind out more\\\\n\\\\nDescription\\\\n\\\\nThe project is being developed and currently owned by Grenergy Renovables. The company has a stake of 100%.\\\\n\\\\nGabriela Solar PV Park is a ground-mounted solar project which is planned over 542 hectares.\\\\n\\\\nThe solar power project consists of 487,872 modules, each with 540W nameplate capacity.\\\\n\\\\nDevelopment status\\\\n\\\\nThe project construction is expected to commence from 2026. Subsequent to that it will enter into commercial operation by 2027.\\\\n\\\\nFor more details on Gabriela Solar PV Park, buy the profile here.\\\\n\\\\nAbout Grenergy Renovables\\\\n\\\\nGrenergy Renovables SL (Grenergy Renovables), is an alternative energy company that generates renewable energy through solar photovoltaic plants. The company offers services such as construction, engineering, and procurement services, project development and independent power producer, among others. It offers services such as project management, plants operations, structuring, and mainten\\\\n\\\\n<error>Content truncated. Call the fetch tool with a start_index of 2000 to get more content.</error>\\\"}]\\nAI: \\nTool: [{\\\"type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Contents of https://www.energy-box.com/post/colbun-begins-permitting-for-usd-500m-solar-and-bess-project-in-chile:\\\\n\\\\n\\\\nColbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS Project in Chile\\\\n\\\\ntop of pageSearch\\\\n# Colbun Begins Permitting for USD 500M Solar and BESS Project in Chile\\\\n\\\\n* Energy Box\\\\n* Jan 2\\\\n* 1 min read\\\\n\\\\nChilean utility Colbun SA has started the environmental permitting process for its Encanto power project in the O'Higgins region. The project aims to develop a 249.7-MWp solar farm coupled with a 260-MW battery energy storage system (BESS).\\\\n\\\\nThe total investment for this project is estimated at USD 500 million (EUR 480.6m), based on Colbun’s permit application.\\\\n\\\\nLocated on private land in the Marchigue commune, the project will feature over 349,000 photovoltaic modules and a battery storage capacity of 1,040 MWh, along with a substation and transmission line.\\\\n\\\\nConstruction is planned to begin in April 2026, pending approval.n.\\\\n\\\\n* SOLAR\\\\n* ENERGY STORAGE\\\\n##