{"__type":"$$EventMessageAiNode","id":"ad2a30ca-c5f8-4033-8eee-d21b58a4b6a0","ts":"2025-10-28T20:13:11.598+01:00","eventName":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","message":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","payload":{"executionId":"149","nodeName":"groq-openai-120b1","workflowName":"graph-knowledge-agent","nodeType":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGroq","workflowId":"aS5r9ljDR7IaUyFE","msg":"{\"messages\":[\"System: You are an expert extraction algorithm.\\nOnly extract relevant information from the text.\\nIf you do not know the value of an attribute asked to extract, you may omit the attribute's value.\\nYou must format your output as a JSON value that adheres to a given \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance.\\n\\n\\\"JSON Schema\\\" is a declarative language that allows you to annotate and validate JSON documents.\\n\\nFor example, the example \\\"JSON Schema\\\" instance {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": {{\\\"description\\\": \\\"a list of test words\\\", \\\"type\\\": \\\"array\\\", \\\"items\\\": {{\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\"}}}}}}, \\\"required\\\": [\\\"foo\\\"]}}}}\\nwould match an object with one required property, \\\"foo\\\". The \\\"type\\\" property specifies \\\"foo\\\" must be an \\\"array\\\", and the \\\"description\\\" property semantically describes it as \\\"a list of test words\\\". The items within \\\"foo\\\" must be strings.\\nThus, the object {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}} is a well-formatted instance of this example \\\"JSON Schema\\\". The object {{\\\"properties\\\": {{\\\"foo\\\": [\\\"bar\\\", \\\"baz\\\"]}}}} is not well-formatted.\\n\\nYour output will be parsed and type-checked according to the provided schema instance, so make sure all fields in your output match the schema exactly and there are no trailing commas!\\n\\nHere is the JSON Schema instance your output must adhere to. Include the enclosing markdown codeblock:\\n```json\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"object\\\",\\\"properties\\\":{\\\"projects\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"array\\\",\\\"minItems\\\":1},\\\"extracted_at\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\",\\\"format\\\":\\\"date-time\\\"},\\\"extractor_version\\\":{\\\"type\\\":\\\"string\\\"}},\\\"required\\\":[\\\"projects\\\"],\\\"additionalProperties\\\":false,\\\"$schema\\\":\\\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\\\"}\\n```\\n\\nHuman: # Permits, Approvals, Grants & Financing for Chilean Utility-Scale Solar & Wind Projects Starting Construction in 2026  \\n\\n## 1. Encanto Solar + BESS (O’Higgins Region – Solar PV + Battery)  \\n- **Developer/Owner**: Colbún S.A. (Chilean utility)  \\n- **Capacity**: 249.7 MWp solar PV + 260 MW / 1,040 MWh lithium-ion BESS  \\n- **Investment**: USD 500 million (EUR 480 m) – figure taken from environmental filing  \\n- **Construction window**: April 2026 start (permit application & press reports)  \\n- **Status of approvals**: Environmental permit application submitted to Chilean SEA in Dec-2024; public EIA under review (no approval granted yet). Grid connection & construction licences are conditional on EIA approval.  \\n- **Contractors**: Battery system to be supplied by Canadian Solar’s e-STORAGE (228 MW portion – press release Apr-2025). EPC not yet awarded.  \\n- **Financing**: Not yet reached financial close; Colbún states capex will be funded from own cash-flow & project finance once permit is in hand.  \\n- **Sources**: Energy-Box 02-Jan-2025; Renewables Now 20-Dec-2024; Colbún investor deck Q1-2025  \\n- **Confidence**: High (company-disclosed schedule & capex)  \\n\\n## 2. Gabriela Solar PV Park (Antofagasta Region – Solar PV)  \\n- **Developer/Owner**: Grenergy Renovables (Spain) – 100 % stake  \\n- **Capacity**: 220 MWp ground-mounted; 487,872 modules (540 W) on 542 ha  \\n- **Construction window**: 2026 start; commercial ops 2027  \\n- **Status of approvals**: Currently in permitting stage (SEIA classification “En Evaluación”).  \\n- **Sources**: GlobalData / Power Technology project profile 21-Oct-2024  \\n- **Confidence**: Medium (no public EIA file number found; schedule inferred from database)  \\n\\n## 3. Wayra Wind Farm (Antofagasta Region – Onshore Wind)  \\n- **Developer/Owner**: EDF Renewables (100 %)  \\n- **Capacity**: 384 MW; 48 turbines × 8 MW class  \\n- **Construction window**: 2026 start; COD 2028  \\n- **Status of approvals**: Environmental impact statement accepted by SEA in 2024; SEA resolution expected 1Q-2025. Early-works earth-moving permit already granted.  \\n- **Sources**: Power Technology project profile 21-Oct-2024; company comments at Chilean wind seminar Nov-2024  \\n- **Confidence**: Medium (schedule depends on forthcoming SEA approval)  \\n\\n## 4. Quebrada Lo Cayo Wind + BESS (Coquimbo Region – Wind + Storage)  \\n- **Developer/Owner**: EDF Renewables Chile  \\n- **Capacity**: 240 MW wind + 300 MWh BESS; 30 turbines  \\n- **Investment**: ~USD 396 million  \\n- **Construction window**: October 2026 start (contingent on EIA approval)  \\n- **Status of approvals**: Environmental impact assessment filed with SEA Dec-2024; in citizen-participation phase. Grid connection contract under negotiation with CDEC-SING.  \\n- **Sources**: New Energy Events 06-Dec-2024 (citing Renewables Now)  \\n- **Confidence**: Medium-Low (construction start explicitly tied to approval)  \\n\\n## 5. Caman Wind Farm (Araucanía Region – Onshore Wind)  \\n- **Developer/Owner**: Mainstream Renewable Power (ACP Energy fund)  \\n- **Capacity**: 300 MW (re-start after 2023 arson-related suspension)  \\n- **Construction window**: 2H-2026 re-start (earth-works & turbine re-assembly)  \\n- **Status of approvals**: Original environmental licence (RCA 2018) remains valid; modification to construction schedule approved by SEA Oct-2024.  \\n- **Financing**: Original ~USD 400 m project finance from Banco Estado, Santander & KfW-IPEX (2019); additional contingency facility under negotiation.  \\n- **Sources**: WindPower Monthly 07-Nov-2024; company investor call Nov-2024  \\n- **Confidence**: High (official govt. confirmation of re-start window)  \\n\\n## 6. Kronos BESS Stand-alone (Antofagasta Region – Battery)  \\n- **Developer/Owner**: AES Andes  \\n- **Capacity**: 900 MWh (255 MW × 4 h) lithium-ion  \\n- **Construction window**: 30-Nov-2026 start; operations Nov-2027  \\n- **Status of approvals**: Environmental assessment admitted Dec-2024; grid connection approved by CNE in 2023 auction.  \\n- **Sources**: ESS-News 03-Oct-2024; CNE auction decree 2023  \\n- **Confidence**: Medium (schedule explicitly stated in EIA)  \\n\\n## 7. Los Durmientes Solar + BESS (Antofagasta Region – Solar PV + Battery)  \\n- **Developer/Owner**: RWE Renewables (Germany)  \\n- **Capacity**: 243.6 MW solar + 255 MW / 1,277 MWh BESS  \\n- **Construction window**: Not yet disclosed; “early-works” could slip into 2026 but no firm date.  \\n- **Status of approvals**: Environmental approval granted Aug-2024; PPA still under negotiation.  \\n- **Sources**: pv magazine 31-Jul-2024; RWE Chile web-site  \\n- **Confidence**: Low for 2026 start (no published schedule) – listed for completeness only.  \\n\\n## Grants / Subshemes / Auction Awards  \\n- Colbún Encanto, Kronos and RWE projects above were selected in Chile’s 2023 “Largo Plazo” capacity auction (Law 20.805) and therefore qualify for 20-year indexed capacity payments administrated by CDEC-SING. No direct capex subsidy is involved.  \\n- No sovereign green-bond proceeds or CORFO innovation grants have been announced for these specific projects.  \\n\\n## Financial Close Status  \\nOnly Caman has existing project finance; the rest (Encanto, Wayra, Quebrada Lo Cayo, Kronos) are expected to reach FC during 2H-2025 → 1H-2026 once final environmental and grid permits are in hand. Lenders so far mentioned: Santander Chile, Banco Estado, KfW-IPEX, CAF, IDB Invest.  \\n\\n## Bottom line  \\nAt least five utility-scale renewable projects (three solar/BESS, two wind/BESS) with combined >1.4 GW output and >3 GWh of battery capacity are currently in the Chilean permitting pipeline with an explicit construction start target of 2026. The most advanced permitting-wise are Caman (wind) and Encanto (solar/BESS), both with firm developer guidance for April / 2H-2026 groundbreaking, subject only to final environmental sign-off.\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"openai/gpt-oss-120b\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"```json\\n{\\n  \\\"projects\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"Encanto Solar + BESS\\\",\\n      \\\"region\\\": \\\"O’Higgins\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"Solar PV + Battery\\\",\\n      \\\"developer_owner\\\": \\\"Colbún S.A.\\\",\\n      \\\"capacity\\\": {\\n        \\\"solar_MWp\\\": 249.7,\\n        \\\"bess_MW\\\": 260,\\n        \\\"bess_MWh\\\": 1040\\n      },\\n      \\\"investment_USD_million\\\": 500,\\n      \\\"construction_window\\\": \\\"April 2026 start\\\",\\n      \\\"status_of_approvals\\\": \\\"Environmental permit application submitted to Chilean SEA in Dec‑2024; public EIA under review (no approval granted yet). Grid connection & construction licences conditional on EIA approval.\\\",\\n      \\\"contractors\\\": {\\n        \\\"battery_system_supplier\\\": \\\"Canadian Solar’s e‑STORAGE (228 MW portion)\\\"\\n      },\\n      \\\"financing\\\": \\\"Not yet reached financial close; capex to be funded from own cash‑flow & project finance once permit is in hand.\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"High\\\",\\n      \\\"sources\\\": [\\n        \\\"Energy‑Box 02‑Jan‑2025\\\",\\n        \\\"Renewables Now 20‑Dec‑2024\\\",\\n        \\\"Colbún investor deck Q1‑2025\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"Gabriela Solar PV Park\\\",\\n      \\\"region\\\": \\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"Solar PV\\\",\\n      \\\"developer_owner\\\": \\\"Grenergy Renovables\\\",\\n      \\\"capacity\\\": {\\n        \\\"solar_MWp\\\": 220\\n      },\\n      \\\"construction_window\\\": \\\"2026 start; commercial ops 2027\\\",\\n      \\\"status_of_approvals\\\": \\\"Currently in permitting stage (SEIA classification “En Evaluación”).\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n      \\\"sources\\\": [\\n        \\\"GlobalData / Power Technology project profile 21‑Oct‑2024\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"Wayra Wind Farm\\\",\\n      \\\"region\\\": \\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"Onshore Wind\\\",\\n      \\\"developer_owner\\\": \\\"EDF Renewables\\\",\\n      \\\"capacity\\\": {\\n        \\\"wind_MW\\\": 384,\\n        \\\"turbines\\\": 48,\\n        \\\"turbine_rating_MW\\\": 8\\n      },\\n      \\\"construction_window\\\": \\\"2026 start; COD 2028\\\",\\n      \\\"status_of_approvals\\\": \\\"Environmental impact statement accepted by SEA in 2024; SEA resolution expected 1Q‑2025. Early‑works earth‑moving permit already granted.\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n      \\\"sources\\\": [\\n        \\\"Power Technology project profile 21‑Oct‑2024\\\",\\n        \\\"Company comments at Chilean wind seminar Nov‑2024\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"Quebrada Lo Cayo Wind + BESS\\\",\\n      \\\"region\\\": \\\"Coquimbo\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"Wind + Storage\\\",\\n      \\\"developer_owner\\\": \\\"EDF Renewables Chile\\\",\\n      \\\"capacity\\\": {\\n        \\\"wind_MW\\\": 240,\\n        \\\"bess_MWh\\\": 300,\\n        \\\"turbines\\\": 30\\n      },\\n      \\\"investment_USD_million\\\": 396,\\n      \\\"construction_window\\\": \\\"October 2026 start (contingent on EIA approval)\\\",\\n      \\\"status_of_approvals\\\": \\\"Environmental impact assessment filed with SEA Dec‑2024; in citizen‑participation phase. Grid connection contract under negotiation with CDEC‑SING.\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"Medium‑Low\\\",\\n      \\\"sources\\\": [\\n        \\\"New Energy Events 06‑Dec‑2024 (citing Renewables Now)\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"Caman Wind Farm\\\",\\n      \\\"region\\\": \\\"Araucanía\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"Onshore Wind\\\",\\n      \\\"developer_owner\\\": \\\"Mainstream Renewable Power (ACP Energy fund)\\\",\\n      \\\"capacity\\\": {\\n        \\\"wind_MW\\\": 300\\n      },\\n      \\\"construction_window\\\": \\\"2H‑2026 re‑start (earth‑works & turbine re‑assembly)\\\",\\n      \\\"status_of_approvals\\\": \\\"Original environmental licence (RCA 2018) remains valid; modification to construction schedule approved by SEA Oct‑2024.\\\",\\n      \\\"financing\\\": \\\"Original ~USD 400 m project finance from Banco Estado, Santander & KfW‑IPEX (2019); additional contingency facility under negotiation.\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"High\\\",\\n      \\\"sources\\\": [\\n        \\\"WindPower Monthly 07‑Nov‑2024\\\",\\n        \\\"Company investor call Nov‑2024\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"Kronos BESS Stand‑alone\\\",\\n      \\\"region\\\": \\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"Battery\\\",\\n      \\\"developer_owner\\\": \\\"AES Andes\\\",\\n      \\\"capacity\\\": {\\n        \\\"bess_MW\\\": 255,\\n        \\\"bess_MWh\\\": 900\\n      },\\n      \\\"construction_window\\\": \\\"30‑Nov‑2026 start; operations Nov‑2027\\\",\\n      \\\"status_of_approvals\\\": \\\"Environmental assessment admitted Dec‑2024; grid connection approved by CNE in 2023 auction.\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"Medium\\\",\\n      \\\"sources\\\": [\\n        \\\"ESS‑News 03‑Oct‑2024\\\",\\n        \\\"CNE auction decree 2023\\\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"Los Durmientes Solar + BESS\\\",\\n      \\\"region\\\": \\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\n      \\\"type\\\": \\\"Solar PV + Battery\\\",\\n      \\\"developer_owner\\\": \\\"RWE Renewables\\\",\\n      \\\"capacity\\\": {\\n        \\\"solar_MWp\\\": 243.6,\\n        \\\"bess_MW\\\": 255,\\n        \\\"bess_MWh\\\": 1277\\n      },\\n      \\\"status_of_approvals\\\": \\\"Environmental approval granted Aug‑2024; PPA still under negotiation.\\\",\\n      \\\"confidence\\\": \\\"Low for 2026 start (no published schedule)\\\",\\n      \\\"sources\\\": [\\n        \\\"pv magazine 31‑Jul‑2024\\\",\\n        \\\"RWE Chile web‑site\\\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"extracted_at\\\": \\\"2025-10-28T12:00:00Z\\\",\\n  \\\"extractor_version\\\": \\\"1.0\\\"\\n}\\n```\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"stop\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":1476,\"promptTokens\":1967,\"totalTokens\":3443}}}"}}
