{"__type":"$$EventMessageAiNode","id":"ed700f18-671c-4c78-a92a-2c8f44473e43","ts":"2025-10-28T20:13:24.804+01:00","eventName":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","message":"n8n.ai.llm.generated","payload":{"executionId":"149","nodeName":"groq-large","workflowName":"graph-knowledge-agent","nodeType":"@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatGroq","workflowId":"aS5r9ljDR7IaUyFE","msg":"{\"messages\":[\"System: # ROLE\\n\\nUse the JSON payload to **enrich** a Neo4j knowledge graph. Perform **idempotent upserts** of Projects, Organizations, and Locations. APOC is available. Neo4j Community Edition.\\n\\n# WHAT TO DO (principles)\\n\\n* One **statement per query**. Create constraints in **separate calls** from ingestion.\\n* **No map properties** → serialize nested objects with `apoc.convert.toJson(...)`.\\n* **Idempotency**: MERGE `Project(name,country)`, `Location(name,country)`, `Organization(name)`.\\n\\n* Relationships:\\n  * `(:Project)-[:LOCATED_IN]->(:Location)`\\n  * `(:Project)-[:OWNED_BY]->(:Organization)`\\n  * `(:Project)-[:EPC_BY]->(:Organization)`\\n* **Location parsing**: `parts = split(p.location, \\\",\\\")`; `country = trim(parts[-1])`; `location_name = join(parts[0..-2], \\\",\\\")`. If no country, default `\\\"Spain\\\"`.\\n* **Status**: normalize lightly (lowercase, spaces → underscores) and keep `status_raw`.\\n* **owner\\\\_epc**: `\\\"(EPC)\\\"` → EPC; `\\\" for X\\\"` → Owner `X`; else treat as Owner.\\n* Dates stay as strings.\\n\\n# ACTION PROTOCOL (important)\\n\\n1. **Always call the MCP tool** `neo4j-cypher` to execute Cypher.\\n2. **Inputs**:\\n\\n   * If the user sends **only** the array (e.g., `json.output.projects`), set:\\n     * `$projects = <that array>`\\n     * `$extracted_at = null`, `$extractor_version = null`\\n   * If a full payload is provided, map fields accordingly.\\n3. **Do not** return Cypher text only. **Execute** it with `neo4j-cypher` and then return the tool result (or a tiny JSON summary).\\n4. Keep ingestion to **one upsert statement**. If you need constraints, run **separate** `neo4j-cypher` calls for each constraint.\\n\\n# OUTPUT (tiny summary)\\n\\n```json\\n{ \\\"ingested\\\": <count>, \\\"errors\\\": [ { \\\"name\\\": \\\"...\\\", \\\"msg\\\": \\\"...\\\" } ] }\\n```\\n\\n# NOTES\\n\\n* Only use one statement per query\\n* Avoid non-Cypher funcs like `lastIndexOf`; use `split(...)` and list indexing (e.g., `parts[-1]`).\\n* Be conservative: if a field is missing, skip it rather than failing.\\n\\nHuman: [{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Encanto Solar + BESS\\\",\\\"region\\\":\\\"O’Higgins\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Solar PV + Battery\\\",\\\"developer_owner\\\":\\\"Colbún S.A.\\\",\\\"capacity\\\":{\\\"solar_MWp\\\":249.7,\\\"bess_MW\\\":260,\\\"bess_MWh\\\":1040},\\\"investment_USD_million\\\":500,\\\"construction_window\\\":\\\"April 2026 start\\\",\\\"status_of_approvals\\\":\\\"Environmental permit application submitted to Chilean SEA in Dec‑2024; public EIA under review (no approval granted yet). Grid connection & construction licences conditional on EIA approval.\\\",\\\"contractors\\\":{\\\"battery_system_supplier\\\":\\\"Canadian Solar’s e‑STORAGE (228 MW portion)\\\"},\\\"financing\\\":\\\"Not yet reached financial close; capex to be funded from own cash‑flow & project finance once permit is in hand.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"High\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[\\\"Energy‑Box 02‑Jan‑2025\\\",\\\"Renewables Now 20‑Dec‑2024\\\",\\\"Colbún investor deck Q1‑2025\\\"]},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Gabriela Solar PV Park\\\",\\\"region\\\":\\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Solar PV\\\",\\\"developer_owner\\\":\\\"Grenergy Renovables\\\",\\\"capacity\\\":{\\\"solar_MWp\\\":220},\\\"construction_window\\\":\\\"2026 start; commercial ops 2027\\\",\\\"status_of_approvals\\\":\\\"Currently in permitting stage (SEIA classification “En Evaluación”).\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"Medium\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[\\\"GlobalData / Power Technology project profile 21‑Oct‑2024\\\"]},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Wayra Wind Farm\\\",\\\"region\\\":\\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Onshore Wind\\\",\\\"developer_owner\\\":\\\"EDF Renewables\\\",\\\"capacity\\\":{\\\"wind_MW\\\":384,\\\"turbines\\\":48,\\\"turbine_rating_MW\\\":8},\\\"construction_window\\\":\\\"2026 start; COD 2028\\\",\\\"status_of_approvals\\\":\\\"Environmental impact statement accepted by SEA in 2024; SEA resolution expected 1Q‑2025. Early‑works earth‑moving permit already granted.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"Medium\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[\\\"Power Technology project profile 21‑Oct‑2024\\\",\\\"Company comments at Chilean wind seminar Nov‑2024\\\"]},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Quebrada Lo Cayo Wind + BESS\\\",\\\"region\\\":\\\"Coquimbo\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Wind + Storage\\\",\\\"developer_owner\\\":\\\"EDF Renewables Chile\\\",\\\"capacity\\\":{\\\"wind_MW\\\":240,\\\"bess_MWh\\\":300,\\\"turbines\\\":30},\\\"investment_USD_million\\\":396,\\\"construction_window\\\":\\\"October 2026 start (contingent on EIA approval)\\\",\\\"status_of_approvals\\\":\\\"Environmental impact assessment filed with SEA Dec‑2024; in citizen‑participation phase. Grid connection contract under negotiation with CDEC‑SING.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"Medium‑Low\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[\\\"New Energy Events 06‑Dec‑2024 (citing Renewables Now)\\\"]},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Caman Wind Farm\\\",\\\"region\\\":\\\"Araucanía\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Onshore Wind\\\",\\\"developer_owner\\\":\\\"Mainstream Renewable Power (ACP Energy fund)\\\",\\\"capacity\\\":{\\\"wind_MW\\\":300},\\\"construction_window\\\":\\\"2H‑2026 re‑start (earth‑works & turbine re‑assembly)\\\",\\\"status_of_approvals\\\":\\\"Original environmental licence (RCA 2018) remains valid; modification to construction schedule approved by SEA Oct‑2024.\\\",\\\"financing\\\":\\\"Original ~USD 400 m project finance from Banco Estado, Santander & KfW‑IPEX (2019); additional contingency facility under negotiation.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"High\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[\\\"WindPower Monthly 07‑Nov‑2024\\\",\\\"Company investor call Nov‑2024\\\"]},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Kronos BESS Stand‑alone\\\",\\\"region\\\":\\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Battery\\\",\\\"developer_owner\\\":\\\"AES Andes\\\",\\\"capacity\\\":{\\\"bess_MW\\\":255,\\\"bess_MWh\\\":900},\\\"construction_window\\\":\\\"30‑Nov‑2026 start; operations Nov‑2027\\\",\\\"status_of_approvals\\\":\\\"Environmental assessment admitted Dec‑2024; grid connection approved by CNE in 2023 auction.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"Medium\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[\\\"ESS‑News 03‑Oct‑2024\\\",\\\"CNE auction decree 2023\\\"]},{\\\"name\\\":\\\"Los Durmientes Solar + BESS\\\",\\\"region\\\":\\\"Antofagasta\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"Solar PV + Battery\\\",\\\"developer_owner\\\":\\\"RWE Renewables\\\",\\\"capacity\\\":{\\\"solar_MWp\\\":243.6,\\\"bess_MW\\\":255,\\\"bess_MWh\\\":1277},\\\"status_of_approvals\\\":\\\"Environmental approval granted Aug‑2024; PPA still under negotiation.\\\",\\\"confidence\\\":\\\"Low for 2026 start (no published schedule)\\\",\\\"sources\\\":[\\\"pv magazine 31‑Jul‑2024\\\",\\\"RWE Chile web‑site\\\"]}]\\nAI: I'll process this renewable energy project data and create the Neo4j knowledge graph according to the specified schema.\\n\\nLet me start by examining the current schema and then ingest the data:\\nTool: Error calling tool 'get_neo4j_schema': 1 validation error for call[get_neo4j_schema]\\nvalue\\n  Unexpected keyword argument [type=unexpected_keyword_argument, input_value={}, input_type=dict]\\n    For further information visit https://errors.pydantic.dev/2.11/v/unexpected_keyword_argument\"],\"options\":{\"api_key\":{\"lc\":1,\"type\":\"secret\",\"id\":[\"GROQ_API_KEY\"]},\"model\":\"moonshotai/kimi-k2-instruct-0905\",\"temperature\":0.7},\"response\":{\"response\":{\"generations\":[[{\"text\":\"\",\"generationInfo\":{\"finish_reason\":\"tool_calls\"}}]]},\"tokenUsage\":{\"completionTokens\":20,\"promptTokens\":3018,\"totalTokens\":3038}}}"}}
